A "memory-bound" operation refers to a process where the system's memory is the primary limiting factor; 
A "significant occurrence" refers to operations that have happened more than 10 times; 
"not instantaneous" refers to operations with a total self-time greater than 0 microseconds; 
"a tenth of a millisecond" is equivalent to 100 microseconds.

sql:
SELECT hlo_op
FROM operations
WHERE total_time_us = (SELECT MAX(total_time_us) FROM operations);

SELECT op_id
FROM operations
ORDER BY total_time_us DESC;
